This paper deals with the problem of 2-dimensional searching for range queries, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and computational geometry. The paper presents solutions for both main and external memory models, which suggests that it could belong to categories related to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The problem of 3-sided range queries involves planar geometry, which suggests that it could also belong to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also presents deterministic data structures, which suggests that it could belong to categories related to algorithms and complexity (cs.DC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
